James S. FRANKLIN, Plaintiff in Error, v. UNITED STATES, Defendant in Error. (Circuit Court of Appeals, Fifth Circuit. March 22, 1926.) No. 4667. C. E. Hardin, of Leesville, La., for plaintiff in error, Philip H. Meeom, U. S. Atty., and J. Pair Hardin, Asst. U. S. Atty., both' of Shreveport, La.

Before WALKER and BRYAN, Circuit Judges, and BURNS, District Judge.

PER CURIAM.

The judgment is affirmed.
